<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#F0DCA0">Originally posted by lar on 01-11-2000 01:29 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">I guess I'll have to do a faq about the faq  ;)
&gt;&gt;
No. 18: Spells. What do you mean by spells will improve if you use them more often ? Does that mean a spell can actually fail in the beginning ? &lt;&lt;

No. It just keeps on getting stronger and better the more you use it.


&gt;&gt;No. 22: Will we be able to write our own comments on the automap ? Or will there be automatic pop-up information for every location ?&lt;&lt;

Both.

&gt;&gt;
11: Do you really mean RUN with a twohanded sword? So as in: take your twohander in both hands, wield it, start screaming and run toward your enemy and strike him if he isn't already scared to death? That would really require great skill.&lt;&lt;

Yep, that exactly what I meant. And yes, it is a rather advanced skill.

&gt;&gt;
During the fight you can freeze the game to enter your commands. Can you do this during conversations, too? Or is there an auto-freeze until you select your phrase? Can those NPCs get impatient if you wait too long till you say something&lt;&lt;

Well, when you are talking time is not frozen, so it is very well possible that some monster passes by.  Maybe I'll make it autofreeze though.

&gt;&gt;
17: Magical weapons: Is there a magic skill to enchant your own weapon? Are there monsters who can only be hit by magical weapons? And, even worse, are there monsters that can only be hit by non-magical weapons? &lt;&lt;

The enchant your weapon skill I hadn't thought of, but it sounds like a cool idea and not too hard to implement. (Maybe balancing might be tricky).  As for the monsters, balancing will determine this. Can't say right now.

&gt;&gt;
21: If I can steal from other NPCs, can they steal from me?&lt;&lt;

It's not a default behavior, but our story system allows it. Probably some editor will put it in for some character if he thinks on it.

&gt;&gt;Hm... just start a contest in this forum &lt;&lt;

Well, actually, Kirill just mentioned a really good name. We'll throw it in the group and see what comes out of it.

&gt;&gt;
What about this story editor? Is it something for an addon? Or did you left it for some unforeseen rush of spare time?&lt;&lt;

It belongs with the multiplayer version, and no, no decision on it has been taken yet.

Lar


</TEXTAREA>
